Q4: Why must matrix multiplication follow: A columns = B rows? (Intuitive)

  - To compute one value in the output matrix:
	  1. Take one row from matrix A
	  2. Take one column from matrix B
	  3. Multiply corresponding elements
	  4. Sum the results

